        "answer_count": 5,
        "title": "why doesn&#39;t instanceof work the way it sounds?",
        "body": "<p>In Java, the <code>instanceof<\/code> operator will only return <code>false<\/code> if comparing <code>null<\/code>. If you test a reference variable that isn't of the required type, the program fails to compile.\nDoes this operator effectively only test if a reference is <code>null<\/code> or not? Or is there another use I'm not thinking of?<\/p>\n\n<p>If not, why not call it <code>isNull<\/code> or something more descriptive?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 8302319,
