    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ffbf4e85b8ffbae4e9039b9c0cf07bc8?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 2496,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 3474,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3474/erickson",
                "reputation": 270535,
                "display_name": "erickson",
                "accept_rate": 83
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 5,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1322515010,
            "creation_date": 1322514599,
            "body": "<p>I'm not sure how you came to your conclusion, but the <code>instanceof<\/code> operation will result in <code>false<\/code> when the runtime type of the first operand does not match the type specified by the second operand.<\/p>\n\n<p>For example, <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Object t1 = \"Hello, World!\";\nSystem.out.println(t1 instanceof Number);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>&hellip; prints \"false\" because t1 is a <code>String<\/code>, not a <code>Number<\/code> or one of its subclasses.<\/p>\n\n<p>Can you please include your example of an <code>instanceof<\/code> operation that failed to compile? Most likely, this is due to a syntax error.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 8302342,
            "question_id": 8302319,
            "last_edit_date": 1322515010
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1660a0fea3ae7e43218919bda2c9ca36?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 72671,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 209725,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/209725/chris-lacasse",
                "reputation": 1582,
                "display_name": "Chris Lacasse"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 4,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1322518027,
            "creation_date": 1322515069,
            "body": "<p>It fails to compile if the comparison can never be true.  For example:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>\"string\" instanceof Number\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>This will not compile because the compiler knows that a string can never be a number.  The operator does exactly what one would expect it to do: it tests if the operand is an instance of the specified type.<\/p>\n\n<p>Returning false when testing a null reference is meant to make the code simpler and more readable.  It prevents you from needing to do this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>if (obj != null &amp;&amp; obj instanceof Number) {\n    ...\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Read this to learn about the operator: <a href=\"http://java.sun.com/docs/books/jls/third_edition/html/expressions.html#15.20.2\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://java.sun.com/docs/books/jls/third_edition/html/expressions.html#15.20.2<\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 8302441,
            "question_id": 8302319,
            "last_edit_date": 1322518027
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5252d061371ebb5944acc4447b455d87?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 383107,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 738746,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/738746/bhesh-gurung",
                "reputation": 51080,
                "display_name": "Bhesh Gurung",
                "accept_rate": 97
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1322515721,
            "creation_date": 1322514664,
            "body": "<p>It's useful when you have a superclass type reference and you want to check if the object is an instance of some subclass:<\/p>\n\n<p>e.g.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Sup { }\n\npublic class Sub1 extends Sup { }\n\npublic class Sub2 extends Sup { }\n\npublic void someMethod(Sup sup) {\n    if(sup instanceof Sub1) {\n        //....\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 8302355,
            "question_id": 8302319,
            "last_edit_date": 1322515721
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/936f8c28b401a914224af1e0e9891633?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 98681,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 266978,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/266978/baltasarq",
                "reputation": 12372,
                "display_name": "Baltasarq",
                "accept_rate": 100
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1322514965,
            "creation_date": 1322514965,
            "body": "<p><code>instanceof<\/code> returns true when you use it agains an instance of the class at its right, or any derived from it. It will return false otherwise.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>class A { /*...*/ }\nclass B extends A { /*...*/ }\n\nA objA = new A();\nB objB = new B();\n\nboolean test = objA instanceof A;   // test is true\ntest = objA instanceof B;   // test is false\ntest = objB instanceof A;   // test is true\ntest = objB instanceof B;   // test is true\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>The code above will not raise any exception. The following will do, however:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>objB = (B) objA;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Hope this helps.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 8302415,
            "question_id": 8302319
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4257f04051c3dce1b84bee2cec359ebe?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 1063248,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1064431,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1064431/katu",
                "reputation": 701,
                "display_name": "Katu",
                "accept_rate": 100
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1322515257,
            "creation_date": 1322515257,
            "body": "<pre><code>if(MyObj instanceof SomeClass)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<ul>\n<li>If left side objet is null= return false<\/li>\n<li>if left side is not instance of rigth side class then return false<\/li>\n<li>if left side is instance if right side then return true<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p>Please note, that instanceof usage can be avoided with polymorphism in most cases.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 8302483,
            "question_id": 8302319
        }
